# Operational Gotchas

This file is the live, high-signal gotchas list used during normal development.
Historical or niche gotchas belong in `gotchas-archive.mdc`.

## Run and History Semantics

### PRISMA checklist source file
The API reads `doc_manuscript.md` from the run directory (not `manuscript.md`).

### Historical run attach behavior
After restart, historical runs are not in `_active_runs`. Use `POST /api/history/attach`
before expecting run-scoped results views to resolve.

### `/api/history/active-run` requires query param
`GET /api/history/active-run` must include `workflow_id`.

### `/api/run/{run_id}` accepts active ids and `wf-*`
Run endpoints resolve either active in-memory session ids or workflow ids from
`runs/workflows_registry.db`.

### RunSession URL restore probes active run before trusting localStorage
On refresh at `/run/:workflowId`, if `loadLiveRun()` matches the URL workflow,
`useRunSessionSync` calls `GET /api/history/active-run?workflow_id=...` first.
When the stored `run_id` no longer matches, it clears localStorage and falls back
to `fetchHistory` + `attachHistory` instead of reconnecting stale SSE.

### Live sidebar card after terminal SSE (`wasStreamingRef`)
`useLiveRunStream` clears `localStorage` on terminal SSE status always, but only
clears React `liveRunId` when the run never reached `streaming` (prefetch-detected
terminal). After a truly live run finishes, the card stays until the next start.

## API and UI Contracts

### Readiness and diagnostics are separate
`/api/run/{run_id}/readiness` and `/api/run/{run_id}/diagnostics` are different surfaces.
Both may expose top-level `audit_summary`, but payload intent is different.

### Config stream is POST
`/api/config/generate/stream` is `POST`, not `GET`.

### `/api/run` is JSON-only
CSV uploads use dedicated multipart endpoints, not `POST /api/run`.

### Setup flow shape
Setup UI is a single question-first flow (not tabbed mode variants).

### Outline/LLM unit tests patch `get_chat_client`, not `PydanticAIClient`
Writing-phase tests monkeypatch `src.writing.outline_generator.get_chat_client` (and
the calling module's import) to return a fake client with `complete_validated`. Patching
`PydanticAIClient.complete_validated` directly no longer works after the chat-client seam.

## Runtime and Operations

### PM2 process names are strict
Use `litreview-api`, `litreview-ui`, `litreview-tunnel` exactly.

### Production serves built assets
Production URL serves `frontend/dist/`; run `pnpm build` before production verification.

### Backend edits require restart
Backend `src/` changes require `pm2 restart litreview-api` to take effect.

## Data and Writing Contracts

### Screening narrative source
`_build_screening_method_description()` in `src/writing/context_builder.py` is canonical.
`_sanitize_body()` in `src/export/markdown_refs.py` does not inject screening disclosure text.

### Canonical included cohort
Use `study_cohort_membership` (`synthesis_eligibility='included_primary'`) as included-study source.

### PRISMA automation exclusions
`automation_excluded` maps to "removed before screening: automation tools", not `other_removed`.

### Citation catalog and lineage
Writing must use cited keys from grounding catalog and preserve citation lineage validity checks.
